\begin_layout Subsection*
Data analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We analyzed the subset (
\begin_inset Formula $n=363)$
\end_inset

 of the ChAT dataset for which eight EEG and four reference channels were
 available for initial and followup recordings, where recordings were uninterrup
ted according to clinical notes, and excluding three children who were not
 awake at recording onset for one session.
 We extracted the first 300 sleeping epochs, and computed fourteen distance
 measures (Table X).
 For each distance measure, we compared the distributions of intra-individual
 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{AA}=d(A_{baseline},A_{followup})$
\end_inset

 to inter-individual distances 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{AB}=d(A_{baseline},B_{followup})$
\end_inset

.
 Measures were considered 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

trait-like
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 if they varied less within an individual than between individuals (
\begin_inset Formula $D_{AA}<D_{AB}$
\end_inset

) according to a t-test (Table X).
 
\end_layout

