\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Spectral power
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We computed spectral power, epochwise, in each of five classical frequency
 bands.
 These hypnographic quantities were normalized to unity maximum (
\begin_inset Formula $x/\max x$
\end_inset

) before transforming to logarithmic coordinates; outliers were then removed
 using the kNN distance, and then time-derivatives were estimated with heavy
 (
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=10^{30})$
\end_inset

 total variation regularization.
 Measures were then computed on the estimated 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{d}{dt}(\log x)=\dot{x}/x$
\end_inset

.
 
